{"abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to add AstronomyKit to your project and perform basic astronomical calculations.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/GettingStarted"},"metadata":{"title":"Getting Started with AstronomyKit","roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"AstronomyKit"}]},"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Essentials","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/TimeAndObservers"],"anchor":"Essentials"}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/astronomykit\/gettingstarted"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"AstronomyKit provides a type-safe Swift interface for astronomical calculations. This article walks you through installation and your first calculations.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Installation","anchor":"Installation","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add AstronomyKit to your Swift package:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["dependencies: [","    .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/heirloomlogic\/AstronomyKit.git\", from: \"0.1.0\")","]"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Or in Xcode: "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"File → Add Package Dependencies","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and enter the repository URL."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Your First Calculations","anchor":"Your-First-Calculations","level":2},{"type":"heading","text":"Import the Package","anchor":"Import-the-Package","level":3},{"type":"codeListing","code":["import AstronomyKit"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","text":"Set Up Your Observer Location","anchor":"Set-Up-Your-Observer-Location","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Most astronomical calculations require an observer location on Earth:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ New York City","let observer = Observer(latitude: 40.7128, longitude: -74.0060)","","\/\/ With elevation (in meters)","let denver = Observer(latitude: 39.7392, longitude: -104.9903, height: 1609)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","text":"Get the Current Time","anchor":"Get-the-Current-Time","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"AstronomyKit uses "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/AstroTime"},{"type":"text","text":" for all time-based calculations:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Current time","let now = AstroTime.now","","\/\/ From a specific date","let newYear = AstroTime(year: 2025, month: 1, day: 1, hour: 12)","","\/\/ From Foundation Date","let fromDate = AstroTime(Date())"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","text":"Calculate a Position","anchor":"Calculate-a-Position","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Find where a celestial body appears in your sky:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Mars in the local sky","let mars = try CelestialBody.mars.horizon(at: .now, from: observer)","print(\"Altitude: \\(mars.altitude)°\")     \/\/ Height above horizon","print(\"Direction: \\(mars.compassDirection)\")  \/\/ N, NE, E, etc."],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","text":"Find the Moon Phase","anchor":"Find-the-Moon-Phase","level":3},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let angle = try Moon.phaseAngle(at: .now)","print(\"\\(Moon.emoji(for: angle)) \\(Moon.phaseName(for: angle))\")","\/\/ Output: 🌔 Waxing Gibbous"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","text":"Get Rise and Set Times","anchor":"Get-Rise-and-Set-Times","level":3},{"type":"codeListing","code":["if let sunrise = try CelestialBody.sun.riseTime(after: .now, from: obser